Vocabulary:
Bodyweight exercises: Exercises that involve using your own body weight for resistance to strengthen muscles and improve fitness.
Lunges: A strength training exercise that involves bending one knee and placing the other foot forward and down on the ground while performing a squat-like motion.
Squats: A strength training exercise that involves standing with your feet hip-width apart, squatting down and returning to the starting position.
Push-ups: A bodyweight exercise that involves pushing your body up off the ground by using your arms and shoulders.
Ab exercises: Exercises that specifically target the abdominal muscles, including crunches, mountain climbers, and planks.
Yoga stretches: A form of exercise that involves various poses and stretches to improve flexibility, strength, and overall health.
Pilates moves: A form of exercise that involves controlled movements that focus on developing core strength and flexibility.
Planks: A bodyweight exercise that involves holding a specific pose for a set period of time, targeting the core muscles.
Form: The proper and correct technique used during an exercise or movement.
Proper form: The correct and proper technique used during an exercise or movement.
Well-ventilated: Having sufficient air flow to keep the environment clean and healthy.
Variety: A wide range of exercises or activities.
Floor mat: A mat placed on the ground for exercising or playing.
Fitness routine: A set of exercises or activities performed in a specific order or frequency to improve physical fitness.
Lighting: The amount of illumination in a particular area or space.
Fitness area: A designated space or area for physical exercise or activity.
Comfortable environment: An environment that is conducive to comfort and relaxation
